remake (0.5-132) unstable; urgency=low

  * Increased project version to 0.5
  * Restructured source tree
    + CMake modules now reside under module directory
    + Script distribution under src/bin
  * New features:
    + Changed version format in remake_project() to MAJOR.MINOR.PATH-REV
    + Added ReMakeDistribute modules for automated project distribution
      (currently supports the Debian distribution standards)
    + Added remake_file_permissions() macro
    + Added ReMakePack archive macros for source and binary packaging
    + Added svn2debcl script for converting Subversion logs into the
      Debian changelog format
  * Bugfixes:
    + Fixed minor issue in remake_target_add_command()
  * Other changes:
    + remake_svn_log() has new parameter TARGET
    + remake_project() issues TARGET ${REMAKE_PROJECT_CHANGELOG_TARGET}
      to remake_svn_log()
    + remake_file_write() has new option LINES
    + CMake documentation generator gendocs now distributed with remake
      package and displaying command line help

